1. TOTh Conference: 8 & 9 June 2017
University Savoie Mont-Blanc (Chamb=C3=A9ry, France)

Deadline for submission of abstracts: 19 February 2017
Notification to authors: 19 March 2017

The TOTh conferences aim to assemble researchers, industrialists,=20
practitioners and, in a more general way, everyone whose interests=20
concern terminology, language, and knowledge engineering. The TOTh=20
program committee consists of the most prominent personalities in the=20
domain, representing more than 20 different nationalities. (with French=20
and English as official languages).

The 11th international TOTh conference will take place on Thursday 8th=20
and Friday 9th June, 2016 at the University Savoie Mont-Blanc (Chamb=C3=A9=
ry,=20
France).

The =E2=80=98Young Researcher=E2=80=99 prize is awarded by the program co=
mmittee during=20
the conference.

2. TOTh Training Session: "The contribution of Ontology to Terminology",=20
6 & 7 June 2017
University Savoie Mont-Blanc (Chamb=C3=A9ry, France).
The TOTh training sessions are organised over two days immediately=20
before the TOTh Conference. They aim to promote collaboration among=20
language and knowledge professionals. The 2017 TOTh training session=20
will focus on =E2=80=98The contribution of Ontology to Terminology=E2=80=99=
, the 2018=20
training session on =E2=80=98The contribution of Linguistics to Terminolo=
gy=E2=80=99.
